{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"91c97969-d853-49ab-9bed-f0eaed64445c","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your crash dump! The `dump-collect` skill I have available is specifically for **collecting** dumps, not analyzing them — so let me give you direct guidance instead.\n\n## Analyzing a .NET Crash Dump\n\nHere are the main tools you can use:\n\n### 1. `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the REPL:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stack of current thread\n- `clrthreads` — list all managed threads\n- `pe` — print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n- `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n### 2. `lldb` with SOS (Linux/macOS)\n```bash\ndotnet-sos install\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\n```\nThen: `clrstack`, `pe`, `clrthreads`, etc.\n\n### 3. WinDbg (Windows)\nLoad the dump, then `!analyze -v` for automatic root-cause analysis.\n\n---\n\n**Quick start recommendation:** Run `dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp`, then type `pe` to print the exception — that's usually the fastest path to the root cause.\n\nWould you like me to install `dotnet-dump` and start analyzing the file for you? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b1396025-eb89-48b3-ae9b-f88250cae897","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. Let me help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.","outputTokens":467,"requestId":"2C42:152429:29D1D04:2E65670:69F94EDC"},"id":"12e660b0-2826-451c-b0eb-9e759a498dea","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:59:07.744Z","parentId":"4283e87e-